    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.22-23_0001a"/>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Monday Jan-19-1959. <hi rend="underline">Hallsville Mo</hi></dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Dr. N<del>ie</del><add>ei</add>har<del>t</del><add>dt</add>,</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Your television course has been so interesting to me.</p>
                
                <p>I purchased a text book in Sept. and have followed the course purely for pleasure and culture.</p>
                
                <p>My husband is a semi-invalid so we are both shut in a good deal. We both graduated from High School in 1910, so we were not attempting to gain any credits. I have been interested in Indian lore all my life and es<del/><add>pe</add>cially since living in the west. Lived in Colorado Springs for twenty five years.</p>
               
                <p>At club meetings
               
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.22-23_0001b"/>
                    
                    on Indian lore I learned that there were <del/><add>o</add>riginally two-hundred and five tribes. I ha<del/><add>v</add>e been trying the last year to learn the names of them all. Have added many new ones in this study course. But I still have only about a hundred.</p>
                
                <p>Your book is wonderful and I have enjoyed your talks and
                    
                <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
                    
                <figure>
                    <figDesc>Stairs and a door, with a tree and pots of flowers</figDesc>
                </figure>
                    
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27.22-23_0002"/>
                    
                    depths of religious thinking.</p>
                
                <p>I am sorry that the course is ending.</p>
                
                <p>Congratulations on the award you won on Missouri Forum</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely</salute>
                    
                    <signed>Mrs R I Mathers</signed>
                    <address>
                        <addrLine>Hallsville</addrLine>
                        <addrLine>Mo</addrLine>
                    </address>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
            
            
